description: |
  With each API call, youï¿½ll need to set request headers, including an OAuth 2.0 access token. Get an access token by using the OAuth 2.0 client_credentials token grant type with your clientId:secret as your Basic Auth credentials. For more information, see Make your first call. You can use your Sandbox access token to try any of the code in this reference.
type: "OAuth 2.0"
describedBy: 
  headers: 
    Authorization: 
      description: |
       Used to send a valid OAuth 2 access token. The token must be preceeded by the word "Bearer".
      example: Bearer _token_
  queryParameters: 
    access_token: 
      description: |
        Used to send a valid OAuth 2 access token. Do not use together with
        the "Authorization" header
settings: 
  authorizationUri: https://www.sandbox.paypal.com/webapps/auth/protocol/openidconnect/v1/authorize
  accessTokenUri: https://api.sandbox.paypal.com/v1/identity/openidconnect/tokenservice
  authorizationGrants: [ code ]
  scopes: ["https://uri.paypal.com/services/invoicing openid https://api.paypal.com/v1/payments/.* https://api.paypal.com/v1/vault/credit-card/.* https://api.paypal.com/v1/vault/credit-card"]